* * * * * /path/to/command
│ │ │ │ │
│ │ │ │ └─ Day of week (0–6) (Sunday = 0 or 7)
│ │ │ └─── Month (1–12)
│ │ └───── Day of month (1–31)
│ └─────── Hour (0–23)
└───────── Minute (0–59)


| Cron Expression | Meaning                                |
| --------------- | -------------------------------------- |
| `* * * * *`     | Run every minute                       |
| `0 * * * *`     | Run at the top of every hour           |
| `0 0 * * *`     | Run every day at midnight              |
| `0 9 * * 1-5`   | Run at 9 AM on weekdays (Mon–Fri)      |
| `*/10 * * * *`  | Run every 10 minutes                   |
| `30 2 * * 1`    | Run every Monday at 2:30 AM            |
| `0 0 1 * *`     | Run on the 1st of every month at 12 AM |
